---
import Sectionhead from "@components/sectionhead.astro";
---

<div id="vision" class="bg-white py-24 sm:py-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <Sectionhead>
          <Fragment slot="title">Our Vision</Fragment>
          <Fragment slot="desc">
            Free engineers from production operations
          </Fragment>
        </Sectionhead>

        <div class="mx-auto mt-16 max-w-4xl">
          <div class="text-center">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-8">
              Democratizing DevOps Excellence
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg leading-8 text-gray-700 mb-12">
              We envision a world where every software team, regardless of size
              or expertise, has access to enterprise-grade DevOps capabilities.
              InfraGPT is building that future.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">
            <div
              class="relative p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100"
            >
              <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg
                    class="h-8 w-8 text-blue-600"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke-width="1.5"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      d="M9.813 15.904L9 18.75l-.813-2.846a4.5 4.5 0 00-3.09-3.09L2.25 12l2.846-.813a4.5 4.5 0 003.09-3.09L9 5.25l.813 2.846a4.5 4.5 0 003.09 3.09L15.75 12l-2.846.813a4.5 4.5 0 00-3.09 3.09zM18.259 8.715L18 9.75l-.259-1.035a3.375 3.375 0 00-2.455-2.456L14.25 6l1.036-.259a3.375 3.375 0 002.455-2.456L18 2.25l.259 1.035a3.375 3.375 0 002.456 2.456L21.75 6l-1.035.259a3.375 3.375 0 00-2.456 2.456z"
                    ></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h4 class="ml-4 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
                  AI-First Approach
                </h4>
              </div>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Transform complex infrastructure management into natural
                conversations. Our AI understands context, learns from your
                environment, and provides intelligent automation that evolves
                with your needs.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div
              class="relative p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 rounded-xl border border-green-100"
            >
              <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg
                    class="h-8 w-8 text-green-600"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke-width="1.5"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      d="M13.5 10.5V6.75a4.5 4.5 0 119 0v3.75M3.75 21.75h10.5a2.25 2.25 0 002.25-2.25v-6.75a2.25 2.25 0 00-2.25-2.25H3.75a2.25 2.25 0 00-2.25 2.25v6.75a2.25 2.25 0 002.25 2.25z"
                    ></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h4 class="ml-4 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
                  Open Source Foundation
                </h4>
              </div>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Built on transparency, community collaboration, and shared
                ownership. Every line of code is open, auditable, and
                extensible. Together, we're creating tools that serve everyone,
                not just the privileged few.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div
              class="relative p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-violet-50 rounded-xl border border-purple-100"
            >
              <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg
                    class="h-8 w-8 text-purple-600"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke-width="1.5"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      d="M3.75 13.5l10.5-11.25L12 10.5h8.25L9.75 21.75 12 13.5H3.75z"
                    ></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h4 class="ml-4 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
                  Composable Architecture
                </h4>
              </div>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Modular by design. Connect existing tools, integrate with any
                workflow, and customize every component. InfraGPT adapts to your
                stack, not the other way around.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div
              class="relative p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50 rounded-xl border border-orange-100"
            >
              <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg
                    class="h-8 w-8 text-orange-600"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke-width="1.5"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      d="M15 19.128a9.38 9.38 0 002.625.372 9.337 9.337 0 004.121-.952 4.125 4.125 0 00-7.533-2.493M15 19.128v-.003c0-1.113-.285-2.16-.786-3.07M15 19.128v.106A12.318 12.318 0 018.624 21c-2.331 0-4.512-.645-6.374-1.766l-.001-.109a6.375 6.375 0 0111.964-3.07M12 6.375a3.375 3.375 0 11-6.75 0 3.375 3.375 0 016.75 0zm8.25 2.25a2.625 2.625 0 11-5.25 0 2.625 2.625 0 015.25 0z"
                    ></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h4 class="ml-4 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
                  Team Empowerment
                </h4>
              </div>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Every developer becomes a DevOps expert. Break down silos,
                accelerate delivery, and create a culture where infrastructure
                excellence is accessible to all team members.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 mt-20">
            Whys of InfraGPT
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            A founder's perspective on the future of infrastructure management
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose prose-lg mx-auto text-gray-700 space-y-8">
          <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
            <p class="text-lg font-medium text-blue-900 mb-2">
              My core belief:
            </p>
            <p class="text-blue-800 italic">
              "In today's world, building and managing software shouldn't be a
              daunting task."
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-lg">
            I've been managing infrastructure for a decade both as a developer
            and as a infrastructure engineer. I've maintained >99% uptime for
            large-scale systems and reduced production costs. At OkCredit I
            reduced cost of serving 2 million MAUs from ₹400,000 to ₹50,000 per
            day. Through this journey, I've seen firsthand how hard it is to
            manage infrastructure for software teams.
          </p>

          <p>
            Today's reality is overwhelming microservices, container
            orchestrators, multi-region deployments, security compliance, and
            now the rise of "vibe coding". We are producing more code than ever.
            All of this lands hot in production, creating an urgent need for
            counterbalance.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">
              The Problem We're Solving
            </h3>
            <p class="text-amber-800">
              Instead of focusing on fixing production issues at 2AM or doing
              boring cost analysis, people should prioritize building amazing
              user experiences and great features. DevOps expertise should be
              accessible and affordable, not a privilege of well-funded teams.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Why AI Agents Are the Answer
          </h3>

          <p>
            The deterministic nature of infrastructure makes it perfect for AI
            agents. Unlike other domains, infrastructure problems have clear
            terminal states. We can determine when we've solved an issue with
            confidence. This is what makes the approach viable.
          </p>

          <p>
            Modern reasoning models can think step-by-step, breaking down
            complex problems into logical steps. Combined with tools and context
            from your entire infrastructure graph who deployed what, when, and
            why - agents can solve problems that traditionally required deep
            expertise.
          </p>

          <div>
            <div
              class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-10"
            >
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">
                Example of workflows it enables
              </h4>
              <ul class="text-green-800 space-y-2">
                <li>Incident response without waking anyone at 2AM</li>
                <li>
                  Automated infrastructure drift detection and PR generation
                </li>
                <li>Cost insights with every infrastructure change</li>
                <li>Continuous security monitoring and remediation</li>
                <li>Knowledge that improves with every problem solved</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-purple-900 mb-3">
                Success Metrics That Matter
              </h4>
              <ul class="text-purple-800 space-y-2">
                <li>Reduced MTTR (Mean Time To Resolution)</li>
                <li>Lower cloud bills month over month</li>
                <li>Higher deployment frequency</li>
                <li>
                  No burnouts, and Engineers focusing on higher-value work
                </li>
                <li>Strong security posture</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
            User Experience Is Everything
          </h3>

          <p>
            Developer primarily use Slack, Github and the terminal for their
            work. We’re building InfraGPT that it integrates directly with
            existing workflows. People should be able agents in a way that feels
            natural. It's like having a agentic teammate.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Why OpenSource</h3>

          <p>
            We believe in the power of open source to drive innovation and
            adoption. By making InfraGPT open source, people know exactly what's
            running in their production environments. It ensures transparency
            and trust in how AI is applied to infrastructure.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              The Future as I think of it
            </h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Over time, agents will become the default for infrastructure
              management. Organizations will start with cost optimization, move
              to incident response, and eventually automate the all repetitive,
              tedious parts. A future where engineers create software while an
              AI quietly keeps production safe.

              <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600" style="text-align: right;">
                — Priyanshu Jain, Founder
              </p>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
          <p class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 mb-6">
            Want to learn more about our journey and vision?
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
            <a
              href="https://pjay.in/writings/ai-in-devops/"
              target="_blank"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 text-white font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors"
            >
              <svg
